<header class="bg-white shadow">
<div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-10 mb-5 sm:px-6">
  <div class="text-center">
    <h1 class=" text-4xlracking-tight font-extrabold text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
      <span class="block">Send your NFTs to battle!</span>
      <span class="block text-3xl text-indigo-600">Find out which NFTs are the most visually desirable</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-3 max-w-md mx-auto text-base text-gray-500 sm:text-lg md:mt-5 md:text-xl md:max-w-3xl">
      Everyone loves to talk about rarity, but what about visual appeal? In a set of thousands of NFTs, which ones do people actually like the <em>look</em> of the most?
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
</header>

<main>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto py-6 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="px-4 py-4 sm:px-0">
      <ul role="list" class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-4 gap-y-8 sm:grid-cols-3 sm:gap-x-6 lg:grid-cols-4 xl:gap-x-8">
      <% @collections.each do |collection| %>
        <li class="relative">
          <%= link_to collection_path(collection.address) do %>
          <div class="group block w-full aspect-w-10 aspect-h-7 rounded-lg bg-gray-100 focus-within:ring-2 focus-within:ring-offset-2 focus-within:ring-offset-gray-100 focus-within:ring-indigo-500 overflow-hidden">
          <% if collection.large_image_url.present? %>
            <img src="<%=collection.large_image_url.sub('s300', 's600') %>" alt="" class="object-cover pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-75">
          <% else %>
          <img src="<%=collection.image_url.sub('s120', 's600') %>" alt="" class="object-cover pointer-events-none group-hover:opacity-75">
          <% end %>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-2 block text-sm font-medium text-gray-900 truncate pointer-events-none"><%=collection.name%></p>
          <% end %>
        </li>
        <% end %>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</main>